(dogs barking
in the distance)

10:29.529 --> 10:31.665
- Josh?
You need to see this.

10:31.699 --> 10:33.834
- Shots rang out today
on Capitol Hill

10:33.867 --> 10:36.169
in a failed
assassination attempt

10:36.203 --> 10:37.604
on the president.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.339
The assailant
has been identified

10:39.372 --> 10:41.308
as Patricia Greenberg,

10:41.341 --> 10:43.510
a crazed stalker
of Josh and Lucy.

10:43.543 --> 10:45.345
BOTH:
Oh, my God.

10:45.378 --> 10:47.447
- Apparently, this
delusional psychopath thought

10:47.480 --> 10:49.783
her act of violence would
somehow get their attention.

10:49.817 --> 10:51.618
- Let me go!

10:51.651 --> 10:53.286
- Police say she was carrying
a copy of the book

10:53.320 --> 10:54.788
Catcher in the Rye,
as well as

10:54.822 --> 10:57.290
a rather dog-eared copy
of Still Alice.

10:57.324 --> 10:58.625
- Get in the car!

10:58.658 --> 11:00.627
- I did this for you,
Josh and Lucy!

11:00.660 --> 11:03.363
Did you get my recipe?

11:03.396 --> 11:06.366
It's baked
Parmesan-crusted chicken.

11:06.399 --> 11:09.136
(Patti shouting indistinctly)

11:09.169 --> 11:10.303
Soda crackers!

11:10.337 --> 11:11.638
- All right, enough is enough.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.140
You have to be
more direct with her.

11:13.173 --> 11:14.474
- Yeah, yeah, you're right.

11:14.507 --> 11:15.642
You're right.
You're right.

11:15.675 --> 11:16.676
- Parmesan chicken!

11:16.710 --> 11:19.046
- But, I will say,
it looks like

11:19.079 --> 11:21.849
the problem's kind of
resolved itself, so...

11:23.250 --> 11:25.385
(snoring)

11:25.418 --> 11:27.054
(bang!)
- Oh, my God!

11:27.087 --> 11:28.722
- Yoo-hoo!
(laughs)

11:28.756 --> 11:30.690
- Jesus Christ!
- I escaped!

11:30.724 --> 11:32.159
(sirens wailing)
(dogs barking)

11:32.192 --> 11:34.361
Now we can hang out again!

11:34.394 --> 11:37.064
- Mom, it's too much.
It's--it's too much!

11:37.097 --> 11:38.732
- What's wrong?

11:38.766 --> 11:40.400
- I don't want to hang out.

11:40.433 --> 11:42.535
Mom, can't you take a hint,
for God's sakes?

11:42.569 --> 11:44.704
- Oh, I thought
we were having fun.

11:44.738 --> 11:46.740
- I was not having fun.
I was pretending to have fun.

11:46.774 --> 11:48.742
You just--you follow us
around everywhere like

11:48.776 --> 11:50.177
some kind of freak, it's...

11:50.210 --> 11:51.344
(tender piano music)

11:51.378 --> 11:52.846
Enough.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.214
- Oh, I see.

11:54.247 --> 11:56.183
Well...

11:56.216 --> 11:58.351
I didn't know
you felt that way...

11:58.385 --> 11:59.419
about me.

11:59.452 --> 12:01.421
*

12:01.454 --> 12:04.091
I'll go home now.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.726
I'll just leave you two alone.

12:06.760 --> 12:09.562
(shackles clanking)

12:09.596 --> 12:12.599
(sirens wailing)
(dogs barking)

12:16.636 --> 12:17.871
- (exhales)
- Okay, you can do this.

12:17.905 --> 12:19.472
Okay, it's gonna be okay.
- Yeah.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.377
Yeah, you're probably right,
I mean, it's not like--

12:24.411 --> 12:26.546
it's not even like
I was that hard on her.

12:26.579 --> 12:28.381
Right? I--

12:28.415 --> 12:29.716
Huh. Yeah.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.419
They're probably
just around back.

12:32.452 --> 12:35.555
(slow bluegrass music)

12:35.588 --> 12:36.890
*

12:36.924 --> 12:39.426
Hey, Tom.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.561
- Lucy. Josh.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.063
- How's--how's Mom doing?

12:43.096 --> 12:46.599
- Afraid your mom
ain't doing so hot, Josh.

12:46.633 --> 12:48.601
Words you said
hurt her pert' bad.

12:48.635 --> 12:50.237
- (sighs)

12:50.270 --> 12:51.638
How--how bad is it?

12:51.671 --> 12:55.408
- Old Momma's heart
is broken.

12:55.442 --> 12:58.411
She ain't no good
to you no more.

12:58.445 --> 13:00.447
Hell, she ain't no good
to herself.

13:00.480 --> 13:02.749
Only one thing left
to do now.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.084
(shotgun cocks)

13:04.117 --> 13:06.253
- Whoa!
Tom, uh--uh--wh--

13:06.286 --> 13:07.420
where's Mom?

13:07.454 --> 13:08.755
- She's out in yonder shed.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.324
*

13:11.358 --> 13:13.093
- Is she frothing at the mouth?

13:13.126 --> 13:14.761
- She's got her night cream on.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.763
It's a special foamy kind
she likes to get

13:16.796 --> 13:19.632
from the high-end section
of Target or,

13:19.666 --> 13:21.601
as we like to call it,
Targét.

13:21.634 --> 13:23.770
Figure I'd--

13:23.803 --> 13:27.274
let her watch one more episode
of Blue Bloods and then--

13:27.307 --> 13:29.109
take her out
to the Yankee Candle,

13:29.142 --> 13:30.443
let her get to browsin',
and then

13:30.477 --> 13:31.678
shoot her in the back
of the head.

13:31.711 --> 13:33.680
- Oh.
No, no, don't shoot her.

13:33.713 --> 13:35.348
What--uh, there's gotta--
there's gotta--

13:35.382 --> 13:36.616
there's gotta be something
I can do.

13:36.649 --> 13:37.817
- No, no.

13:37.851 --> 13:39.452
She's my wife.

13:39.486 --> 13:40.487
I'll kill her.

13:40.520 --> 13:41.688
- No!
Okay, look,

13:41.721 --> 13:44.157
this--this whole thing
is my fault.

13:44.191 --> 13:45.792
I--I clearly
just should have been

13:45.825 --> 13:47.694
more direct with her
to start with.

13:47.727 --> 13:50.630
I--I should just go
talk to her,

13:50.663 --> 13:52.132
right?

13:52.165 --> 13:53.366
Uh--okay.

13:53.400 --> 13:56.303
(sighs and sputters)

13:56.336 --> 13:58.705
(dramatic music on TV)
- Hey, Pop.

13:58.738 --> 14:01.141
I know I've been the only
member of our entire family

14:01.174 --> 14:03.476
that's not employed
by the NYPD,

14:03.510 --> 14:05.145
but that's not the case
anymore.

14:05.178 --> 14:09.816
*

14:09.849 --> 14:12.219
- Hot dog.

14:12.252 --> 14:14.154
That means our entire family

14:14.187 --> 14:16.356
is affiliated with the NYPD.

14:16.389 --> 14:17.690
Congratulations, son.

14:17.724 --> 14:19.559
(gentle music)

14:19.592 --> 14:21.594
- Stay tuned
for more Blue Bloods.

14:25.198 --> 14:27.367
- How's my favorite mom doing?

14:27.400 --> 14:31.338
(tender music)

14:31.371 --> 14:33.173
I--I'm--I'm sorry,

14:33.206 --> 14:35.208
Mom, I never should
have called you a freak.

14:35.242 --> 14:37.677
- Well, that's not why
I'm upset.

14:37.710 --> 14:40.347
I'm upset because
my own son

14:40.380 --> 14:41.714
doesn't want to see me.

14:41.748 --> 14:44.184
- Oh, no, no, I do,
I do want to see you, Mom.

14:44.217 --> 14:46.353
I do want to see you.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.255
Just...

14:48.288 --> 14:50.357
not all the time.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.525
- Well, how often, then?

14:52.559 --> 14:54.727
Once a week?

14:54.761 --> 14:56.863
- More like once a month.

14:56.896 --> 15:00.533
*

15:00.567 --> 15:04.204
- (sniffs)
Well, that's not so bad.

15:04.237 --> 15:05.705
Holidays too.

15:05.738 --> 15:08.441
- Well, of course holidays too.
You're my mother.

15:08.475 --> 15:09.542
My mother.

15:09.576 --> 15:10.543
(gunshot)

15:10.577 --> 15:11.711
Right, he's--got a gun.

15:11.744 --> 15:13.246
- Whoopsie daisy!

15:13.280 --> 15:15.082
- Jesus Christ.
- Oh! (laughs)

15:15.115 --> 15:17.384
The hair trigger
on this thing.

15:17.417 --> 15:19.552
My God--hey,
Josh, Lucy, you're not

15:19.586 --> 15:22.222
driving by Presbyterian General
on your way?

15:22.255 --> 15:24.224
If you were,
I--I'd take a ride

15:24.257 --> 15:26.059
and maybe hop out
at the old E.R. there?

15:26.093 --> 15:27.560
I seem to have
obliterated my knee.

15:27.594 --> 15:29.396
- Yeah, we can
definitely take you, Tom.

15:29.429 --> 15:30.897
- Oh, should I grab
some celery sticks

15:30.930 --> 15:32.432
and ranch for the road?

15:32.465 --> 15:34.401
- Yeah, okay, that's, um, uh,

15:34.434 --> 15:36.803
yeah, fine, well, um...
(stammering)

15:36.836 --> 15:38.638
Uh, no. No.

15:38.671 --> 15:40.107
Actually, no,
thank you.

15:40.140 --> 15:41.774
Uh--Mom.

15:41.808 --> 15:44.577
I--I don't actually like
ranch dressing very much.

15:44.611 --> 15:45.778
(gentle guitar music)
- Huh.

15:45.812 --> 15:47.480
- Well, that's fine.

15:47.514 --> 15:49.149
More for us.
- Yeah.

15:49.182 --> 15:50.483
- So, uh, we'll see you
at our place,

15:50.517 --> 15:52.119
uh, next month?

15:52.152 --> 15:53.420
- I can't wait.

15:53.453 --> 15:55.088
*

15:55.122 --> 15:56.089
(gunshot)
- Oh, whoops!

15:56.123 --> 15:58.425
- Jesus!
- Oh, wow.

15:58.458 --> 16:00.793
I did it again,
right in the same spot.

16:00.827 --> 16:02.129
- Tom.

16:02.162 --> 16:04.097
- Yeah, I should not
have reloaded.

16:04.131 --> 16:05.765
- No!
- No.

16:05.798 --> 16:06.766
- See you soon, Patti.
- Okay, bye.

16:06.799 --> 16:08.101
- Yeah, see you soon.

16:08.135 --> 16:09.436
- Bye-bye now.
- Take care.

16:09.469 --> 16:11.104
- It's just one big
flesh tube now, huh?

16:11.138 --> 16:14.341
- Yep, okay, all right,
buddy boy, here we go.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.178
(dramatic music)

16:18.211 --> 16:19.846
- You've come
to the right place.

16:19.879 --> 16:21.848
Josh and Lucy's apartment
is a crude and primitive world,

16:21.881 --> 16:24.517
but in some ways, beautiful.

16:24.551 --> 16:26.286
Now, what would you say
if someone showed you

16:26.319 --> 16:30.123
these curtains and said
they got them for only $200?

16:30.157 --> 16:31.991
- Well, I'd laugh
and I'd say I could have got

16:32.025 --> 16:35.462
them for free from my basement.
- (chuckling)

16:35.495 --> 16:38.031
- The proper
ceremonial response is,

16:38.065 --> 16:39.966
"Wow, cool curtains.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.501
Are they from Etsy?"

16:41.534 --> 16:43.170
- Cool curtains.
Are they from Etsy?

16:43.203 --> 16:44.471
- Let's move on.

16:44.504 --> 16:47.340
Now, Tom, what would you do
if I put this in front of you?

16:47.374 --> 16:49.209
(dramatic music pounds)

16:49.242 --> 16:50.543
- I'd eat it.

16:50.577 --> 16:52.479
- Wrong.
- Shit. Shit.

16:52.512 --> 16:55.148
- The correct answer
is that you photograph the food

16:55.182 --> 16:56.483
and then if there's time,
you eat it,

16:56.516 --> 16:57.984
but that is by far secondary.

16:58.017 --> 17:00.019
- We have to go.
It's 9:00 p.m.

17:00.053 --> 17:02.389
- But I thought you said
we were having dinner.

17:02.422 --> 17:05.225
- 9:00 p.m. is dinner.
Shit!

17:05.258 --> 17:07.060
(dramatic musical flourish)

17:07.094 --> 17:08.995
- Get in here, you two.
- Hi!

17:09.028 --> 17:11.164
- Hello. Good to see you.
- Hey, Tom.

17:11.198 --> 17:13.833
Patti, hi, how are you?
- Oh, Lucy, hello.

17:13.866 --> 17:16.336
- Nice to see you.
I hope you guys like tofu curry.

17:16.369 --> 17:18.171
- I look forward to
taking a picture of it

17:18.205 --> 17:19.906
before I eat it.

17:19.939 --> 17:21.007
- Oh.
- Mm.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.875
- Ooh, nice curtains.

17:22.909 --> 17:24.043
Are they from Etsy?

17:24.077 --> 17:25.345
- You know what?
They are!

17:25.378 --> 17:26.846
How did you know?
Come on in, come on in.

17:26.879 --> 17:28.515
- So glad you could make it.

17:28.548 --> 17:29.582
(Walter Martin's
"We're All Young Together")

17:29.616 --> 17:31.384
- * The new kid on my street

17:31.418 --> 17:32.852
- I can't believe we've got

17:32.885 --> 17:35.021
13 members of our family
in the NYPD.

17:35.054 --> 17:37.257
- Actually, it's 12,
since Johnny got shot.

17:37.290 --> 17:40.026
*

17:40.059 --> 17:41.394
- * We like to sing

17:41.428 --> 17:43.563
* This song in harmony

17:43.596 --> 17:47.400
* And her mama sings too

17:47.434 --> 17:50.870
* And the old man
taps his shoe *

17:50.903 --> 17:54.541
* Music's like shampoo

17:54.574 --> 17:57.244
* I need it every morning

17:57.277 --> 17:59.546
* Yes, I do

17:59.579 --> 18:02.615
* And we're all young
together *

